Package bio.singa.structure.model.interfaces

Interface Structure

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AtomContainer, ChainContainer, LeafSubstructureContainer
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MmtfStructure, OakStructure
    public interface Structure
extends LeafSubstructureContainer, ChainContainer
    Structures represent chemical objects in three dimensional space.

    Structures may contain one ore more Models that represent the same structure but in different situations (e.g. at different time steps for MD trajectories or dynamics for NMR)
    Structures may contain one or more Chains that represent one continuous macro molecule (most often the biggest macro molecules and its ligands are collected in one model).
